hcp_name: IHS/PTL  Confederated Tribes of Siletz Indians Hlth Ctr
description_of_services_requested: Post I. This HCP (site) is part of a network of Indian Health Service locations that will be awarded to one bidder. Proposals shall comply with the relevant requirements from Section C.2 and the requirements of Section C.3 of the GSA Networx Universal and Enterprise RFP, the full text of which is provided at http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/104870. If the bidder holds a Networx Universal or Networx Enterprise contract with GSA, it is sufficient to indicate that the services will provided under that contract; otherwise, proposals must respond to the requirements from the Networx Universal RFP. Post II. This HCP currently procures these services under the GSA Networx Universal Contract The circuit must be available 24x7x365. Support for Telecommunications Service Priority (TSP) restoration is required. The circuit must support at least four QoS (Quality of Service) service classes and match the DSCP QOS bits currently used by IHS. Provide connectivity to a MPLS private network that can support two different Verizon MPLS VRF networks and point to point connections. Provider can scale the service logically from a single DS0 to a OC3 based on requirements at  each required IHS site. With T1 circuits, the provider should allow bandwidth upgrades by bonding up to six T1 circuits with symmetrically traffic load balancing across all circuits. With DS3 circuits, the vendor should offer tiered data rates, starting at 8 MBits/s with 2 MBit increments upgrades. To support the required telecommunication services, the provider should be able to offer the following local access methods: Analog Trunk Circuits, ISDN BRI Circuits, Analog Circuits, ISDN PRI Circuits, Digital T-1 Circuits. These access methods should be capable of integrating with on-premise PBX systems or with Centrex PBX-like service where switching is provided at the central office instead of at the customer's premises. Contact Cynthia Ortega (503) 414-7758, cynthia.ortega@ihs.gov.

description_of_services_requested: Post I. HCP is part of a network of Indian Health Service locations that will be awarded to one bidder. Proposals shall comply with the relevant requirements from Section C.2 and requirements of Section C.3 of the GSA Networx Universal and Enterprise RFP, the full text which is at http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/104870. If bidder holds a Networx Universal or Networx Enterprise contract with GSA, it is sufficient to indicate services will be provided under that contract; otherwise, proposals must respond to requirements from Networx Universal RFP. Post II. HCP currently procures these services under GSA Networx Universal Contract. The circuit must be available 24x7x365. Support for Telecommunications Service Priority (TSP) restoration required. Circuit must support at least 4- QoS (Quality of Service) service classes. Provide connectivity to MPLS private network that can support two Verizon MPLS VRF networks and point to point connections. Provider can scale service logically from single DS0 to OC3 based on requirements at each IHS site. Connectivity through Satellite services will also be considered. With T1 circuits, provider should allow bandwidth upgrades by bonding up to 4-T1 circuits with symmetrically traffic load balancing across all circuits. With DS3 circuits, vendor should offer tiered data rates, starting at 8 MBits/s with 2 MBit increments upgrades.  With Ethernet circuits, the provider should offered tiered service, starting at 50Mbits. To support required telecomm services provider should be able to offer the following local access methods: Analog Trunk Circuits, ISDN BRI Circuits, Analog Circuits, ISDN PRI Circuits, Digital T1 Circuits. These access methods should be capable of integrating with on-premise PBX systems or with Centrex PBX-like service where switching is provided at central office. Post III.
